{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a47c2f6e-2e77-4a8d-9d36-1f5d1d8b7210",
    "name": "22 - Admin Signup & Login (API only)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "description": "Flux complet pour creer un admin et se connecter uniquement via l'API (sans UI).\n\nDeux niveaux d'admin:\n\n1) SCHOOL_ADMIN = admin d'une ECOLE\n   - Cree via /api/register/v2 (requetes 01a / 01b).\n   - Peut valider/rejeter UNIQUEMENT les livres SCHOOL de son ecole.\n\n2) DG_M4M / TECH_SUPPORT = admin de la PLATEFORME (super-admin)\n   - Ne peut PAS etre cree via /api/register/v2 pour des raisons de securite.\n   - Se cree via le script: npm run admin:create -- --email ... --name ... --password ...\n   - Peut valider/rejeter N'IMPORTE QUEL livre (GLOBAL + toute ecole).\n   - Voir la requete '99 - NOTE creer un DG_M4M' pour la commande exacte.\n\nApres creation (quel que soit le role), le login se fait pareil:\n   CSRF -> POST /api/auth/callback/credentials -> cookie de session -> GET /api/auth/session."
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "00 - Health check",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "health"]
        }
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "01a - Creer l'admin (auto-referencement d'ecole)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200 ou 201', () => pm.expect([200, 201]).to.include(pm.response.code));",
              "",
              "try {",
              "  const json = pm.response.json();",
              "  if (json?.user?.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', json.user.id);",
              "  if (json?.createdSchool?.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('schoolId', json.createdSchool.id);",
              "} catch (e) { /* ignore */ }"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"{{adminName}}\",\n  \"email\": \"{{adminEmail}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{adminPassword}}\",\n  \"role\": \"SCHOOL_ADMIN\",\n  \"isCreatingSchool\": true,\n  \"newSchoolData\": {\n    \"name\": \"{{newSchoolName}}\",\n    \"type\": \"{{newSchoolType}}\",\n    \"address\": \"{{newSchoolAddress}}\",\n    \"city\": \"{{newSchoolCity}}\",\n    \"country\": \"{{newSchoolCountry}}\"\n  }\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/register/v2",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "register", "v2"]
        },
        "description": "Creer un compte SCHOOL_ADMIN ET son ecole en meme temps.\nL'ecole est creee avec status PENDING, l'utilisateur est owner + admin."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "01b - Creer l'admin (ecole existante)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200 ou 201', () => pm.expect([200, 201]).to.include(pm.response.code));",
              "try {",
              "  const json = pm.response.json();",
              "  if (json?.user?.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', json.user.id);",
              "} catch (e) { /* ignore */ }"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"{{adminName}}\",\n  \"email\": \"{{adminEmail}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{adminPassword}}\",\n  \"role\": \"SCHOOL_ADMIN\",\n  \"schoolId\": \"{{schoolId}}\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/register/v2",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "register", "v2"]
        },
        "description": "Rattacher le nouvel admin a une ecole deja validee (schoolId fourni).\nL'ecole doit etre en status VALIDATED sinon l'API refuse."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "02 - NextAuth CSRF token",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "try {",
              "  const json = pm.response.json();",
              "  if (json?.csrfToken) pm.collectionVariables.set('csrfToken', json.csrfToken);",
              "} catch (e) { /* ignore */ }"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/csrf",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "auth", "csrf"]
        },
        "description": "Recupere le csrfToken NextAuth + pose le cookie next-auth.csrf-token.\nObligatoire avant l'appel credentials."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "03 - Login (Credentials)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200 (NextAuth JSON mode)', () => {",
              "  pm.expect([200, 302]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
              "});",
              "",
              "const setCookie = pm.response.headers.get('Set-Cookie');",
              "if (setCookie) {",
              "  const match = setCookie.match(/next-auth\\.session-token=([^;]+)/);",
              "  if (match) pm.collectionVariables.set('sessionTokenCookie', match[1]);",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" },
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "urlencoded",
          "urlencoded": [
            { "key": "csrfToken",  "value": "{{csrfToken}}",     "type": "text" },
            { "key": "identifier", "value": "{{adminEmail}}",    "type": "text" },
            { "key": "password",   "value": "{{adminPassword}}", "type": "text" },
            { "key": "callbackUrl","value": "{{baseUrl}}/",      "type": "text" },
            { "key": "json",       "value": "true",              "type": "text" },
            { "key": "redirect",   "value": "false",             "type": "text" }
          ]
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/callback/credentials",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "auth", "callback", "credentials"]
        },
        "description": "Authentification par identifiant (email ou telephone) + mot de passe.\nLe cookie next-auth.session-token est pose automatiquement par Postman si 'Automatically follow redirects' est actif."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "04 - Verifier la session active",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "",
              "try {",
              "  const json = pm.response.json();",
              "  pm.test('Role est SCHOOL_ADMIN', () => {",
              "    pm.expect(json?.user?.role).to.eql('SCHOOL_ADMIN');",
              "  });",
              "  if (json?.user?.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', json.user.id);",
              "} catch (e) { /* ignore */ }"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/session",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "auth", "session"]
        },
        "description": "Retourne la session courante si l'utilisateur est authentifie, ou {} sinon."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "05 - Test protege (admin) - file de validation des livres",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/books/admin/pending?page=1&limit=20",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "books", "admin", "pending"],
          "query": [
            { "key": "page",  "value": "1"  },
            { "key": "limit", "value": "20" }
          ]
        },
        "description": "Exemple d'endpoint admin: un SCHOOL_ADMIN voit les livres SCHOOL en attente de validation.\nDoit repondre 200 si le cookie de session est bien envoye automatiquement par Postman."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "06 - Logout",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "urlencoded",
          "urlencoded": [
            { "key": "csrfToken",   "value": "{{csrfToken}}", "type": "text" },
            { "key": "callbackUrl", "value": "{{baseUrl}}/",  "type": "text" },
            { "key": "json",        "value": "true",          "type": "text" }
          ]
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/signout",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "auth", "signout"]
        }
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "99 - NOTE creer un DG_M4M (admin plateforme)",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "health"]
        },
        "description": "Le role DG_M4M (ou TECH_SUPPORT) = admin de la PLATEFORME. Il peut valider N'IMPORTE QUEL livre (GLOBAL ou SCHOOL, toutes ecoles). Il n'est volontairement PAS exposé par /api/register/v2.\n\nCreation via script (recommande):\n\n   cd quizlock-api\n   npm run admin:create -- \\\n     --email admin.plateforme@xkorienta.cm \\\n     --name \"Admin Plateforme\" \\\n     --password \"MonMotDePasseSolide!2024\" \\\n     --role DG_M4M\n\n   # Option --role TECH_SUPPORT disponible aussi.\n   # Si l'email existe deja, le script PROMEUT l'utilisateur sans toucher au mot de passe.\n\nCreation manuelle en base (fallback):\n\n   db.users.updateOne(\n     { email: 'admin.plateforme@xkorienta.cm' },\n     { $set: { role: 'DG_M4M', isActive: true } }\n   )\n\nUne fois cree, connecte-toi avec le flux 02 -> 03 -> 04 ci-dessus en utilisant l'email et le mot de passe choisis. Tu auras alors acces a:\n   - GET  /api/books/admin/pending  (TOUS les livres en attente)\n   - POST /api/books/:id/approve    (n'importe quel livre)\n   - POST /api/books/:id/reject     (n'importe quel livre)\n   - POST /api/admin/books/config   (configuration plateforme)"
      },
      "response": []
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl",           "value": "http://localhost:3001", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "adminName",         "value": "Admin Principal",        "type": "string" },
    { "key": "adminEmail",        "value": "admin@ecole-demo.test",  "type": "string" },
    { "key": "adminPassword",     "value": "Admin1234!",             "type": "string" },
    { "key": "newSchoolName",     "value": "Ecole Demo",             "type": "string" },
    { "key": "newSchoolType",     "value": "SECONDARY",              "type": "string" },
    { "key": "newSchoolAddress",  "value": "12 rue de la Demo",      "type": "string" },
    { "key": "newSchoolCity",     "value": "Douala",                 "type": "string" },
    { "key": "newSchoolCountry",  "value": "Cameroun",               "type": "string" },
    { "key": "schoolId",          "value": "",                       "type": "string" },
    { "key": "userId",            "value": "",                       "type": "string" },
    { "key": "csrfToken",         "value": "",                       "type": "string" },
    { "key": "sessionTokenCookie","value": "",                       "type": "string" }
  ]
}
